<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-344-137  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 344 137.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer-Aided Engineering  Jan 1990 v9 n1 p20(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Cut-and-paste drawing with symbol library. (The Block Librarian bySoftSource) (CAE in Action)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Upscale Design, a consulting firm involved in the preparation ofelectrical and instrumentation design drawings, gives high marksto SoftSource's Block Librarian computer graphics software.andP;  Usingthis add-on package, Upscale Design's engineers can create AutoCADsymbol repositories organized into libraries that can be browsedfrom within an AutoCAD work drawing.andP;  The libraries contain pagesthat can be viewed in grids of 100 blocks.andP;  The act of picking asymbol returns a user to the AutoCAD drawing, restoring scale androtational prompts.andP;  In addition to providing a cut-and-pasteconvenience that saves time in the completion of drawings, BlockLibrarian makes it easy to relocate little-used libraries to otherstorage devices such as Bernoulli Box cartridges.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Upscale Design (computer programs)SoftSource (marketing).andO;Product:   Block Librarian (Computer graphics software) (usage)AutoCAD (CAD software) (computer programs).andO;Topic:     Computer GraphicsComputer-Aided DesignInformation Storage and Retrieval.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>